    <abstract>
      <t>MPLS Network Action (MNA) allows MPLS packet to carry instruction and data for in-network services and functions in an MPLS network. This document describes the FEC-based optimized operations on the MPLS label stack when the network is mixed with LSRs which are capable or incapable of processing MNAs.</t>
